My guess is that if we try to preserve backwards compatibility with apps that might be using `Package.com.company.foo` is that we should check if `className` starts with `Package.`. If it doesn't we inject `Package.`.

```
String packageClassName = className.startsWith("Packages.") ? className :  "Packages." + className;
String expression = String.format("importClass(%s)", packageClassName);
```

